<title>UK: Kalamazoo in bid talks as Lynx bows out.</title>
<headline>Kalamazoo in bid talks as Lynx bows out.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Kalamazoo Computer Group Plc said on Thursday that it was still in merger talks despite the withdrawal of Lynx Holdings Plc from current discussions.</p>
<p>It said that it had received a number of approaches from companies that might bid for Kalamazoo.  </p>
<p>&quot;The board continues to investigate the Kalamazoo Trusts' ability to accept an offer,&quot; said the firm in a statement.</p>
<p>Lynx announced earlier today that it was bowing out of merger talks with Kalamazoo, saying it was &quot;disappointed at the slow rate of progress&quot;.</p>
<p>By 1128 GMT, shares in Kalamazoo were 3-1/2p lower at 84p.</p>
